5:
Something wrong, Alk? I think Tor
Leleni's office is just up ahead.
9:
Oh, it's nothing. I was just looking
around. There's just something
about being in a school like this...
16:
And who might you three be? You're
in the way!
20:
My apologies. Would you happen to
be a student at this school?
25:
We have a message for Professor
Tor Leleni. Do you know if she's
around?
30:
...As a matter of fact, I do—because
that's me!
39:
What's with that look on your face?!
Do you have a problem with that?!
And did you just refer to me as a
STUDENT?!
41:
You land walkers are all the same!
Always treating us sheephirds like
children... That form of
discrimination is not permitted here!
45:
Oh no, I'm so sorry! That's really not
what we meant...
48:
Hmph. Apology accepted—as long
as you're more careful from now on!
We sheephirds are proud of who we
are and what we look like!
52:
But even Lilie and Lelucia don't look
that young—
58:
That's because we're not all the
same!
63:
A-anyway! We came all the way
here on a request from the Guild!
They wanted your help with
re-energizing some gems—
67:
Oh, is it time for that already? I'm
afraid that might prove difficult right
about now...
71:
Unless... Aha, I've got it!
Would you be interested in some
side work?
79:
Listen up! We've got some guests for
today! I'll need you all to be on your
best behavior!
89:
They'll be helping out with class
today. Speaking of which, today's
lesson will be on techniques for
re-energizing elemental gems!
92:
Professor Leleni, you're looking super
cute today, as always!
96:
Yes, yes, thank you!
All right, I'll be passing out the gems
now...
99:
Hey, Professor... Is that guy over
there your boyfriend?
103:
How dare you even suggest that! For
one, he's far too young for me!
106:
But never mind that! More
importantly, I need you to show
more respect and stop asking such
crude questions! Understood?!
109:
All right, you three. That'll be your
job—keep this group of rowdy kids
at bay and help me get through this
lecture without a hitch!
112: That is not going to be an easy task...
115:
Bye, Professor Leleni! See you again
tomorrow!
117:
Yes, yes. Remember to go straight
home! And when you get there,
make sure to review everything we
learned today!
121:
Great work today, you three! Thanks
to you, it looks like I'll be able to
deliver these energized gems to the
Guild on time!
124:
It was the students who did the real
work.
128:
Yes, because they actually did the
lesson for once! They usually just
slack off during the whole
class—hence all the delays.
132:
That was quite the experience...
Things were flying everywhere at
one point... Poor Light got tossed
around like a ragdoll.
136:
Yes, class with them is often like
that. But honestly... I can understand
why they act that way.
137:
The textbooks here really aren't
meant for children of that age, you
see...
140:
Voluntas Academy was originally a
place where the brightest minds in
the land congregated—it's no
surprise they brought such
impenetrable literature.
144:
It's great that we're catering to
younger students now as well, but
we simply lack the right textbooks
for them...
148:
You weren't kidding... There's a lot of
difficult words in here.
151:
I really wanted to have books that
were more accessible to children...
But I've been having trouble finding
any.
156: I may be able to help.
163:
Now hold on a moment! Aren't you
going to explain how you got me
here? Was that teleportation
magic?!
171:
Welcome to Starview Village,
Professor Leleni.
174:
I think you can find the books you
are looking for here.
178:
This is amazing! There are books
that even I've never seen before!
181:
Look at this one! Yes, yes, it has
loads of illustrations—nice and
accessible!
185:
I'm back! I'm here to find some more
new books for the kids!
189:
Wait, already? Didn't you just go
back with a big pile?
193:
Yes, I did... But it turns out I
underestimated those kids!
197:
"Wow Professor Leleni, way to pick
out a book for toddlers! Were YOU
gonna read that?!" Gah, those
impertinent—
201:
I need to find just the right book for
them this time! That'll show them!
205:
...She certainly does complain a lot,
but it's clear that she cares deeply
for her students.
208: Yeah. She really is a great teacher.
212:
Just you wait and see! I'm going to
make my class so good that they'll
be BEGGING me to take it!
